export const questionObj = {"Qtext": "
 
What number should be added to each of the numbers \(7 \), \(14 \), \(19 \), and \(24 \) to make them proportional.
\newline

", "Steps": [{"id": "s1", "n_params": 0, "step_txt": "Lets suppose that the required number is $y $.

Since the numbers $7 + y $, $14 + y $, $19 + y $, $24 + y $ are in proportion, we have
\[
	\frac{7 + y }{14 + y } = \frac{19 + y }{24 + y }
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow (7 + y )(24 + y ) = (14 + y )(19 + y )
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow 168 + y (31 ) + y ^2 = 266 + y (33 ) + y ^2
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow y (31 - 33 ) = 266 - 168 
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow y = \frac{266 - 168 }{31 - 33 }
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow y = \frac{98 }{-2 }
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow y = \frac{-49 }{1 }
\]
\newline

"}]} 

 export const resp = [{"data": [], "text": ""}]
